      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "cases classified as Undetermined. The mean age at first consultation for patients with 5α-reductase type 2 deficiency is reported",
      "bbox": [
        15,
        643,
        580,
        655
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "as 9.6 years, with a standard deviation of 7.5 years, indicating a relatively broad age range from early childhood to late",
      "bbox": [
        15,
        658,
        580,
        670
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "adolescence. In contrast, individuals with PAIS present at an average age of 8.0 years, while those in the Undetermined category",
      "bbox": [
        15,
        674,
        580,
        686
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "consult at an even younger average of 2.5 years. The significant p value of 0.02 suggests a statistically meaningful difference in",
      "bbox": [
